                    <msContents>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            
                            <title type="incomplete">Prayers</title>
                            <note>Prayers to the Trinity, Jesus Christ and Our Lady Mary and against the devil. 
                                The prayers are taken from biblical books and from pseudoepigrapha, i.e.: the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1309Didesq"/> (<locus target="#9"/>), 
                                <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1376Apocal"/> (<locus target="#15"/>), and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1340EnochE"/> (<locus target="#5 #12"/>). 
                                The prayers to Our Lady Mary are entitled <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4298Taamho">Taʾamḫotā la-Māryām</ref> 
                                (cp. <bibl>
                           <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1899Manoscritti"/>
                           <citedRange unit="page">632</citedRange>
                        </bibl>).
                            </note>
                        </msItem>
